Superstar duo Peter and Paul Okoye famously known as P’square has said that considering their years of constantly shunning out hit songs, they have gone beyond the ‘legend’ status. The duo made this statement on stage during their recent performance at the national finals of the Glo Battle of The Year in Lagos. P’square noted they’ve been in the industry way before it got in the present shape and has been on top of their game till date even.   What I’ll do to ladies ‘eyeing’ my new boo…     E-money sponsors singer Portable to London     Komba teams up with Broda Shaggi in ‘Sierra Leone…   “P’square no dey do shows, we no dey do concerts, we dey do crusade so when you think of using the word Legendary, use Ancestors. “Wetin we never do for this stage? We don sing we don dance, my people e easy?” they said as the DJ played their 2011 monster hit track ‘E no easy’.